premise_source_doc_sentence: The Fujitsu iPAD is a lightweight handheld device that was introduced by Fujitsu , in 2002 .
Some trademark analysts estimate that Apple paid Fujitsu over US$ 4 million in exchange for the March 17 , 2010 assignment of Fujitsu 's iPad trademark rights to Apple .
They also designed a microprocessor that was canceled when the division was closed by Fujitsu , known as the SPARC64 V. Fujitsu would later develop a microprocessor with the same name .

Fujitsu Siemens Computers had a presence in key markets across Europe , the Middle East and Africa , while products marketed elsewhere were sold under the Fujitsu brand , with the services division extending coverage up to 170 countries worldwide .
